598 Flaminiae sc. viae, the great north road running through Umbria from Rome to Ariminum. That the read and not the province that bore the name Flaminia is here meant is shown by Zumpt, Observ. xiii. The expression Flaminiae regionibus is doubtless used in a vague and general sense for the parts of the province of Tuscia and Umbria that were in the direction of or adjoining the Flaminian Way.
